Data license — routing tile blocks
===================================

This project's CODE is licensed under LGPL-3.0-or-later (see `LICENSE`).

The generated ROUTING DATA — every `*.tiles` block produced by the generation
pipeline, and any hosted data block distributed from this project — is a
DERIVATIVE DATABASE of OpenStreetMap and is licensed separately:

    © OpenStreetMap contributors
    Open Database License (ODbL) v1.0
    https://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/1-0/

What this means:

- **Attribution** — any use or display of the data (or a work produced from it,
  such as a matched route) must credit "© OpenStreetMap contributors".
- **Share-Alike** — if you distribute a modified/adapted version of the data
  block (a Derivative Database), you must make it available under ODbL too.
- You may use, host, and redistribute the blocks, including commercially; you may
  not relicense the DATA under a more permissive or proprietary license.

Because the generation pipeline in this repository is open, the ODbL obligation
to "make the derivative database available" is satisfied by the public source +
tooling: anyone can rebuild the blocks from public OpenStreetMap data.

Baked elevation (`h`) is derived from public terrain sources (Tilezen/Terrarium,
itself composed from SRTM, NED, and other open data — see `ATTRIBUTION.md`).
Curated foot/cycle route membership derives from OpenStreetMap route relations
(also ODbL).

The full ODbL 1.0 text is at the URL above; this file is a notice, not a
substitute for it.
